description: Singer and actor Tyrese Gibson is the subject of a police warrant for his arrest after police say his pack of dogs mauled a puppy to death in an #Atlanta neighborhood.
title: Cops Say Tyrese Gibson's Dogs Killed Puppy #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Malcolm Jamal Warner's mother spoke candidly with Inside Edition about the heartbreaking moment she learned that her son had died. Pamela Warner says Malcolm's best friend told her that he died and "that just took me to a whole other world." The mother shared with Inside Edition the pain of losing a child. Several stories have surfaced around the circumstances of Malcolm's drowning on a beach in Costa Rica on July 20. Pamela recalled that last time they spoke.
title: Malcolm Jamal Warner's Mom Opens Up About Moment She Learned He Died

author: Inside Edition
description: An instant noodle challenge inspired by "KPop Demon Hunters" has doctors issuing a #warning about the rise in burn injuries.
title: 'KPop Demon Hunters'-Inspired Ramen Challenge Could Lead To Burns #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: A disabled man on a mobility scooter and a Serve Robotics cart collided after the man says the cart repeatedly cut him off. The incident occurred in West Hollywood where there are plenty of Serve Robotics carts that are primarily autonomous, loaded with food and out for delivery. The company says the robots are designed to "navigate respectfully around all people" and in this case "the robot… came to a full stop after attempting to cede the right of way."
title: Disabled Man In Mobility Scooter Upset After Serve Robotics Cart Clash

author: Inside Edition
description: Taylor Swift grew up in a Georgian colonial-style house outside Reading, Pennsylvania. Tracy Panase and her family have lived in the house for the past three years. The home has had several owners since the Swifts and stories about the artist have been passed down. Now Panase, with the help of party planner Marley Majcher, is turning her home into a party central for Swifties to celebrate the midnight release of "The Life of a Showgirl."
title: A Look Inside Taylor Swift's Childhood Home

author: Inside Edition
description: Six homes collapsed one after the other from Mother Nature's fury. It all happened in the span of 45 minutes. It was the result of coastal flooding that hit the outer banks of North Carolina from hurricanes Humberto and Imelda. Christy Roberson's home was swept away. She owned it for 20 years. Storms have been causing beach erosion for years.
title: Several North Carolina Homes Collapse Due To Coastal Flooding

author: Inside Edition
description: Two best friends were riding an e-bike before they were fatally mowed down. Police accuse the driver of deliberately ramming into the girls as they rode home from a school event. Police say it was a cold-blooded murder and the suspect targeted one of the girls because she had spurned him. Maria Niotis and Isabella Salas, both 17, were killed. The suspect, a minor, has been arrested and charged with two counts of first-degree murder.
title: 2 Best Friends Fatally Mowed Down By Accused Stalker: Cops

author: Inside Edition
description: Hawks are predators, but these two became prey for a thief, according to their owner, who is desperate to get them back. Charles Cogger is a falconer and tells KCBS he was working with his birds at SoFi Stadium in Los Angeles at the Rams game. His trained hawks chase away other birds like crows who like to steal food from fans. That's where he says someone took his utility truck with the two hawks in their boxes. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Reward Offered After 2 Hawks Stolen At SoFi Stadium In Los Angeles
